1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:08,240
♪

2
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:11,160
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:11,160 --> 00:01:44,280
♪

4
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:50,050
(gunshot)

5
00:01:50,050 --> 00:01:52,000
(gasping)

6
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,210
(clinking)

7
00:01:54,210 --> 00:01:55,280
Sayo?

8
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,290
-(gunshot)
-Ah!

9
00:01:58,230 --> 00:02:00,260
Say...Sayo.

10
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,110
♪

11
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:12,070
So, this is how it feels
to have you holding me,

12
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:13,280
here in your arms.

13
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:18,010
Mmm...mmm.

14
00:02:18,010 --> 00:02:22,050
I never told you...

15
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:24,290
...how much you mean to me.

16
00:02:24,290 --> 00:02:28,080
I wish I had before now.

17
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:31,080
(coughing)

18
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:33,000
Oh, no!

19
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,010
No, Sayo!

20
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:45,190
♪

21
00:02:47,230 --> 00:02:50,230
(panting)

22
00:02:50,230 --> 00:03:05,040
♪

23
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:08,040
(panting)

24
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:16,190
♪

25
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:19,170
That's impossible, Kenshin isn't
really serious about this.

26
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:23,000
He can't fight Shogo
without his sight.

27
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:25,080
Oh, Kenshin.

28
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:28,270
Again, Kenshin?

29
00:03:28,270 --> 00:03:32,040
Do you think you can
actually defeat me sightless?

30
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:34,080
Yes, Shogo, I can.

31
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:38,210
I will because that's the only
way to bring you to your senses.

32
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:42,160
For these people to live,
you must surrender.

33
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:48,260
♪

34
00:03:48,260 --> 00:03:52,090
Artillery and infantry ready,
awaiting your command, sir.

35
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:55,060
Be prepared to begin
the assault upon my command.

36
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:56,170
Yes, sir!

37
00:03:56,170 --> 00:04:00,020
How many times do I have to tell
you, don't attack Holy Hill.

38
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:03,020
Kenshin Himura's over
there fixing things!

39
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:05,010
What do I have to do,
rip your legs off

40
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:07,190
to get your attention
just so you'll listen?

41
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:09,020
What's she saying, Captain?

42
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:11,150
I'm saying Kenshin's
on Holy Hill right now,

43
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:13,270
talking to Shogo Amakusa.

44
00:04:13,270 --> 00:04:18,020
I'm telling you there's no need
for innocent people to die!

45
00:04:18,020 --> 00:04:20,090
Place this woman
under military arrest.

46
00:04:20,090 --> 00:04:23,180
Oh, pretend you have a brain,
don't destroy Shimabara!

47
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:25,020
What does it take
to get through

48
00:04:25,020 --> 00:04:27,050
your armor-plated
military skulls?

49
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:28,220
(grunting)

50
00:04:28,220 --> 00:04:31,070
Release that young
lady immediately!

51
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:33,030
-Huh?
-Oh.

52
00:04:33,030 --> 00:04:37,130
♪

53
00:04:37,130 --> 00:04:39,180
It's you, Governor Elsten.

54
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:42,260
Consul Elsten, we
welcome your presence.

55
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:45,150
Governor, I come to warn you.

56
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:47,210
You must immediately
bring to a halt the assault

57
00:04:47,210 --> 00:04:49,270
on the village
of Shimabara, sir.

58
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,230
Huh?

59
00:04:50,230 --> 00:04:53,010
This act of unwarranted
violence can harm

60
00:04:53,010 --> 00:04:55,080
our international relationship.

61
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:59,070
My government views this
action with great concern.

62
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:00,270
With all due respect,
Mr. Elsten, you have

63
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:02,020
no right to interfere.

64
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:04,070
This is purely an
internal matter.

65
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:08,130
Any action that we take is
strictly our own concern, sir.

66
00:05:08,130 --> 00:05:11,090
But not, sir, when you set about
murdering innocent people

67
00:05:11,090 --> 00:05:13,070
merely because the faith
they believe in

68
00:05:13,070 --> 00:05:15,130
happens to be Christian.

69
00:05:15,130 --> 00:05:18,080
For hundreds of years,
ever since the Edo era,

70
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:21,050
you have been following
this path of awful oppression.

71
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:23,060
It must stop.

72
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:25,040
But times are difficult, sir.

73
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:29,160
I don't speak for
my government alone.

74
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:33,040
America, England, and France--

75
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:36,070
the entire international
community views this persecution

76
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:38,210
of Christians with
extreme disfavor.

77
00:05:38,210 --> 00:05:41,190
If you continue, there could be
the most severe consequences

78
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:44,040
to your entire nation.

79
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:47,140
Are you prepared to fight
against the entire world?

80
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:48,230
Well, sir?

81
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:50,110
Will you listen?

82
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:52,110
I know I'm just a girl,
and I'm not supposed to know

83
00:05:52,110 --> 00:05:55,070
about these things, but the
whole world's watching us.

84
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:56,200
If you massacre
these Christians,

85
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:59,200
it could lead to full scale war,
and in case you haven't noticed,

86
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,050
we aren't that big!

87
00:06:01,050 --> 00:06:04,160
If that happens,
you're responsible.

88
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:08,220
Shogo Amakusa is a dangerous
fanatic who has broken the law.

89
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:11,140
His religion is not the issue,
only the subversive acts

90
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:13,230
he's planning to commit
against the government.

91
00:06:13,230 --> 00:06:16,150
And that's exactly why
Kenshin Himura is up there

92
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:19,210
right now convincing
him to surrender.

93
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:22,130
I firmly believe this
can be solved peacefully.

94
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:24,210
Mr. Himura is famous
as a Royalist

95
00:06:24,210 --> 00:06:26,280
of the Meiji Restoration.

96
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:30,060
I think he can achieve
surrender without bloodshed.

97
00:06:30,060 --> 00:06:33,020
Attacking these Christian
people would be a mistake, sir.

98
00:06:33,020 --> 00:06:36,170
Mr. Elsten, there are many
factors at work here, sir.

99
00:06:36,170 --> 00:06:39,150
Captain?

100
00:06:39,150 --> 00:06:43,030
This is a military matter,
which is really not your affair.

101
00:06:43,030 --> 00:06:45,290
Rebellion against the government
is punishable by death.

102
00:06:45,290 --> 00:06:47,010
No.

103
00:06:47,010 --> 00:06:49,040
You're crazy.

104
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,040
However, I will do this for you.

105
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:54,040
You seem to think this Kenshin
can perform miracles.

106
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,120
Very well, let him.

107
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:59,100
I will give him one hour to
arrange Shogo's surrender.

108
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:02,080
But if he fails, we attack.

109
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:04,140
Lieutenant, prepare to
move out in one hour.

110
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:05,200
One hour, sir.

111
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,120
And if there's the
slightest resistance,

112
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,130
we will crush it to death.

113
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:10,260
Good day, sir.

114
00:07:10,260 --> 00:07:13,170
(sighing)

115
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:18,110
♪

116
00:07:18,110 --> 00:07:20,040
If you can't get
Shogo to surrender,

117
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,290
then they'll all be massacred.

118
00:07:22,290 --> 00:07:27,140
A blind man to save
a madman from another madman.

119
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:29,100
Oh, Kenshin.

120
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:30,240
What's going on?

121
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,030
Shogo has been challenged.

122
00:07:32,030 --> 00:07:33,180
Isn't that Kenshin Himura?

123
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:36,080
Yes, but I heard
he lost his sight.

124
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:38,010
Maybe he wants
Lord Shogo to heal him.

125
00:07:38,010 --> 00:07:41,000
No, it was Lord Shogo that
blinded him in the first place.

126
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,270
Some people don't know
when they're ahead.

127
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:44,280
Maybe we should take
the children away.

128
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:48,240
After that, I can't believe
he'd come back here.

129
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,200
You're telling me to surrender,

130
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,010
ordering me to.

131
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:57,060
(chuckling)

132
00:07:57,060 --> 00:08:00,030
(laughing)

133
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:11,080
No one gives orders to
Shogo Amakusa, no one!

134
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:14,250
To think that I would ever stand
still for such humiliation.

135
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:17,000
My death will be proud and holy,

136
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,090
and all of my followers
will join me in Heaven.

137
00:08:20,090 --> 00:08:24,060
No, Shogo, that's not what
you believe in your heart.

138
00:08:26,030 --> 00:08:28,030
Just what do you mean?

139
00:08:28,030 --> 00:08:29,120
It's strange.

140
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:31,270
Even though my eyes
can't see your face,

141
00:08:31,270 --> 00:08:35,190
my blindness helps me see
more clearly into your heart.

142
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:38,060
The truth is in there.

143
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:41,270
I've seen that truth, Shogo,
since our katanas crossed

144
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:44,060
on the night of thunder cry.

145
00:08:44,060 --> 00:08:44,455
Huh?

146
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:51,090
That night, your Hiten Mitsurugi
technique achieved a perfection

147
00:08:51,090 --> 00:08:53,200
that was almost beyond human.

148
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,040
Almost.

149
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:59,010
Each sword stroke shocked me
with an indescribable power.

150
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:02,260
Your passion and your
strength were fueled

151
00:09:02,260 --> 00:09:05,160
by the very essence
of Mitsurugi.

152
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:09,170
In your final stroke, its power
took the blood from my flesh,

153
00:09:09,170 --> 00:09:12,140
the fire from my arms,

154
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:15,070
the sight from my eyes.

155
00:09:15,070 --> 00:09:17,140
♪

156
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:21,200
That's when I saw your spirit--
the will, the need, the desire

157
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,190
to give others protection.

158
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:26,270
The death of another
kills a part of you.

159
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:29,230
My heart saw the truth
in your heart.

160
00:09:29,230 --> 00:09:32,110
Even if the life is
taken from an enemy,

161
00:09:32,110 --> 00:09:36,290
your soul weeps tears
of blood at the loss.

162
00:09:36,290 --> 00:09:41,160
You try to be so cold,
your speech sounds hard,

163
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:44,000
unyielding as stone,

164
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:47,190
but sometimes you can't
frighten an enemy away.

165
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:49,270
You have no choice but to kill,

166
00:09:49,270 --> 00:09:53,120
and oh, the price you pay.

167
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:56,160
You expect me to believe you
could possibly lead these people

168
00:09:56,160 --> 00:10:00,130
to their deaths without knowing
full well the consequences?

169
00:10:00,130 --> 00:10:03,010
Recognizing you will spend
all of eternity suffering

170
00:10:03,010 --> 00:10:05,240
unspeakable grief
because of what you did,

171
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:07,070
the lives you lost?

172
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:09,120
This is Hiten Mitsurugi.

173
00:10:10,210 --> 00:10:14,120
Himura, you know--
you know the pain

174
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:18,180
and the grief that I feel
every single day that I awaken.

175
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:20,140
The grief of knowing my destiny

176
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:24,080
is to take those lives
whether I want to or not.

177
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,110
♪

178
00:10:26,110 --> 00:10:31,070
That's exactly why I must
do something, Shogo.

179
00:10:31,070 --> 00:10:33,070
(panting)

180
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:36,120
♪

181
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,010
Oh, Kenshin.

182
00:10:38,010 --> 00:10:39,190
Very well, then.

183
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:41,070
You leave me no
choice but to test

184
00:10:41,070 --> 00:10:44,010
your mastery of the
Hiten Mitsurugi style.

185
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:45,220
I'm sorry.

186
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:50,140
♪

187
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:52,010
I decide when I die.

188
00:10:52,010 --> 00:10:54,130
First, I will defeat you.

189
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:57,150
That will be my last miracle.

190
00:10:57,150 --> 00:11:01,160
Then, on this holy day,
I will fight the murdering army,

191
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:03,230
and at a time
that I choose,

192
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:07,110
I will die and go to
Heaven with my followers.

193
00:11:07,110 --> 00:11:11,240
♪

194
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,050
Double time, march!

195
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:19,210
Forward, quickly!

196
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:21,280
Mr. Elsten, we've
got to do something.

197
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:24,190
I'm going up the hill right now
to see if Kenshin has talked

198
00:11:24,190 --> 00:11:26,290
Shogo into surrendering yet.

199
00:11:26,290 --> 00:11:28,190
I'll give you a signal
from up there.

200
00:11:28,190 --> 00:11:31,050
Then, do everything you
can to stop the attack.

201
00:11:31,050 --> 00:11:33,170
Mmm hmm, good luck to you.

202
00:11:33,170 --> 00:11:35,170
(panting)

203
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:38,290
♪

204
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:42,000
(panting)

205
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:49,130
♪

206
00:11:49,130 --> 00:11:50,200
It's beginning.

207
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:53,060
The battle of two
Mitsurugi masters.

208
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:55,000
If Kenshin can
defeat Shogo here,

209
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,100
the Seal of Rai Ryu Sen
will be broken.

210
00:11:57,100 --> 00:12:02,100
And what's even more important,
Kenshin will regain his sight.

211
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:03,230
Kori, I don't get it.

212
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:05,170
How is Kenshin
supposed to fight anyone

213
00:12:05,170 --> 00:12:07,050
if he can't see his opponent?

214
00:12:07,050 --> 00:12:08,280
How can he defend
himself from Shogo

215
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:10,270
if he's got that
sort of handicap?

216
00:12:10,270 --> 00:12:12,190
It won't be easy.

217
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:14,000
He should be able to remember

218
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,220
some of Shogo's
movement patterns.

219
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:19,170
Remember that they did fight
once before and they're both

220
00:12:19,170 --> 00:12:22,140
champion swordsmen
in Hiten Mitsurugi.

221
00:12:22,140 --> 00:12:24,140
-And also--
-And also...?

222
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:25,240
Well, Kenshin's luck.

223
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,140
You know what
Kenshin always says:

224
00:12:27,140 --> 00:12:30,040
"It's smarter to be lucky
than it's lucky to be smart."

225
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,120
But Kenshin is lucky.

226
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:33,210
He's pretty smart.

227
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:35,230
I just hope his luck holds out.

228
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:37,180
It absolutely has to.

229
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:38,260
There are too many lives

230
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:40,230
depending on the
outcome of this.

231
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:42,130
It has to!

232
00:12:42,130 --> 00:12:58,020
♪

233
00:12:58,020 --> 00:13:00,270
Kenshin, you're defeated!

234
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:08,010
♪

235
00:13:08,010 --> 00:13:09,000
Huh?

236
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,260
Ha, he stopped Shogo!

237
00:13:10,260 --> 00:13:14,020
Twin dragon blocking
twin dragon!

238
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:16,170
Surrender, Shogo.

239
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,000
No, never!

240
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,290
Never--my choice, my choice!

241
00:13:19,290 --> 00:13:23,290
(grunting)

242
00:13:23,290 --> 00:13:25,240
I can sense that
you're bleeding,

243
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,030
but I didn't strike you.

244
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:29,060
That's not your concern, Himura.

245
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:36,010
(panting)

246
00:13:36,010 --> 00:13:38,120
Get up, Shogo.

247
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:41,060
Kenshin Himura is every bit
as good as Lord Shogo,

248
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:43,120
even if he is blind.

249
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:48,010
How could he wound Lord Shogo
without even using his blade?

250
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:51,290
Shogo, I know you've been shot,

251
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:54,030
and now your blood
stains the ground.

252
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:55,040
Stop now.

253
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:57,000
Oh, you're a talkative one.

254
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,210
You're trying to distract me
from the business at hand,

255
00:13:59,210 --> 00:14:03,290
which is your death!

256
00:14:03,290 --> 00:14:07,170
Are you still trying to paint
yourself as God's chosen one?

257
00:14:07,170 --> 00:14:09,130
Your body is
wounded and bleeding

258
00:14:09,130 --> 00:14:11,260
just like your spirit
is wounded and bleeding.

259
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:14,050
The massacre of your mother
and father wounded you

260
00:14:14,050 --> 00:14:16,020
because you could do
nothing to stop it.

261
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:18,260
You decided the only way to help
others was to convince them

262
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:20,290
divine power flows through you,

263
00:14:20,290 --> 00:14:24,000
but all you've really done
is hurt them by playing God.

264
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:24,389
Shut up!

265
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,190
(groaning)

266
00:14:30,190 --> 00:14:32,010
Oh, my gosh!

267
00:14:32,010 --> 00:14:35,040
♪

268
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,200
It's agony that
you're not really God.

269
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:41,020
You suffer that you can't save
those who believe in you.

270
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:45,180
Failure, guilt that you could
not save your sister's life--

271
00:14:45,180 --> 00:14:49,220
no, Shogo, you're not
allowed to have that guilt.

272
00:14:49,220 --> 00:14:51,280
You wanted your sister
and all these people here

273
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:54,190
to be completely
happy now, on Earth,

274
00:14:54,190 --> 00:14:57,070
but that's not in
the power of a mere man.

275
00:14:57,070 --> 00:15:01,240
You can't just make people
happy by wishing it to be so.

276
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:05,100
Remember Shogo, you said
that there's happiness eternal

277
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:09,250
and unending to be
found in Heaven.

278
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:12,100
Well, there's just
one small problem.

279
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:15,270
To achieve that, all of your
followers have to be killed off.

280
00:15:15,270 --> 00:15:18,100
And you're a holy man,
you don't kill anymore,

281
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:21,040
but the army does and the army's
willing to help all these people

282
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:23,100
off the Earth and up to Heaven.

283
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:25,160
And you're willing
to let them do it.

284
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:28,280
All because you can't face
the fact that you're not God.

285
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:30,280
You're just a man, Shogo.

286
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:33,020
♪

287
00:15:33,020 --> 00:15:37,210
Be a man...face yourself.

288
00:15:37,210 --> 00:15:40,180
(breathing weakly)

289
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:46,270
So, Shogo, you've
finally come to visit me.

290
00:15:46,270 --> 00:15:50,080
It's the first time
since you took my sight.

291
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:53,090
This proves to me that you now
know that prideful actions

292
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:56,160
will gain you nothing
but more pain.

293
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:58,130
How much longer
will you dare to claim

294
00:15:58,130 --> 00:16:00,190
the title of God's Chosen One?

295
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:03,120
It is a heavy burden,
so are you positive

296
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,130
that you can carry its weight?

297
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,230
It's not a problem for me.

298
00:16:06,230 --> 00:16:10,060
It helps to give my life
a lot more direction.

299
00:16:10,060 --> 00:16:13,040
This is my power,
to save the people,

300
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:15,190
to baptize them into the truth.

301
00:16:15,190 --> 00:16:18,130
With Amakakeru Ryu no Hirameki.

302
00:16:18,130 --> 00:16:21,040
Shogo, why won't
you understand?

303
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:23,260
You're bright,
you had such promise.

304
00:16:23,260 --> 00:16:26,130
But your Amakakeru
Ryu no Hirameki

305
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:28,010
is based in hatred.

306
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:30,180
Your mind is clouded
with self-doubt.

307
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:32,070
One day you'll be defeated

308
00:16:32,070 --> 00:16:37,050
by one who does not need
eyes to see the truth.

309
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:40,050
(panting)

310
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:43,160
♪

311
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:47,000
Kenshin Himura, the time
has come to see who is right,

312
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,250
whether it's you or me.

313
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:51,160
Our blades will decide.

314
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:53,140
So, prepare to die.

315
00:16:53,140 --> 00:16:57,000
There is no way your
Amakakeru Ryu no Hirameki

316
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:01,000
can stand against my
Amakakeru Ryu no Hirameki.

317
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:12,080
♪

318
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:13,080
It's true!

319
00:17:13,080 --> 00:17:17,020
Shogo's actually going
to go through with it.

320
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:18,130
Kenshin also.

321
00:17:18,130 --> 00:17:22,180
Two masters of
Amakakeru Ryu no Hirameki.

322
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:26,100
♪

323
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:30,080
It's up to you to choose
your own path, your decision.

324
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:32,270
Kenshin, please
take care of Shogo.

325
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:36,250
He will need your help...please.

326
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:39,010
♪

327
00:17:39,010 --> 00:17:42,020
Everything I am must
go into this blade.

328
00:17:42,020 --> 00:18:18,020
♪

329
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:29,100
Shogo, you must be
prepared to someday

330
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:31,160
give everything
to save Shimabara.

331
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,180
I will!

332
00:18:34,210 --> 00:18:37,080
Protect those who have
been mistreated, my son.

333
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:40,000
Forget pity--
be strong, Shogo,

334
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,210
strong as the steel of a blade.

335
00:18:42,210 --> 00:18:46,040
I will...I will be
strong with no pity.

336
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:49,040
I'll fight bad people
and help good people.

337
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:50,230
I'll save everyone.

338
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:52,040
I will.

339
00:18:52,290 --> 00:18:54,180
What have I done?

340
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:56,090
Who have I fought?

341
00:18:56,090 --> 00:18:58,250
I've drawn steel
against people I love,

342
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:01,080
and deserted people who love me.

343
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:05,020
I've failed to save
those closest to me.

344
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:07,150
Don't worry, sister,
I'll always keep you safe.

345
00:19:08,260 --> 00:19:12,110
I was much happier
then than I realized.

346
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:15,080
I knew nothing about hate.

347
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:17,060
When did I learn it?

348
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:19,070
When did I give up my innocence?

349
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:21,270
♪

350
00:19:21,270 --> 00:19:24,140
When did I lose
my faith in others?

351
00:19:24,140 --> 00:19:26,280
And when did I lose myself?

352
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:29,180
What did I forget
about humanity?

353
00:19:29,180 --> 00:19:33,070
And what did I
willingly throw away?

354
00:19:33,070 --> 00:19:35,160
I can never go back.

355
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:39,030
I'm lost...lost.

356
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:43,260
♪

357
00:19:43,260 --> 00:19:46,110
Oh, no, he's dead, he's dead!

358
00:19:46,110 --> 00:19:47,210
He was invincible!

359
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:49,040
(indistinct chatter)

360
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,220
Whoa!

361
00:19:51,220 --> 00:19:53,190
(gasping)

362
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:57,020
♪

363
00:19:57,020 --> 00:20:00,160
(gasping for air)

364
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:03,250
Finish it...go ahead.

365
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:06,260
Right now...finish it.

366
00:20:06,260 --> 00:20:08,100
It's over.

367
00:20:09,290 --> 00:20:12,150
I'm no good to
anyone any longer.

368
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:14,160
I can't save anyone.

369
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:17,080
I'm not God's child,
I'm not a holy man.

370
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:20,140
I'm not a healer--
just a man.

371
00:20:20,140 --> 00:20:22,170
Good to no one.

372
00:20:22,170 --> 00:20:25,000
Ohh.

373
00:20:26,170 --> 00:20:29,160
Oh, please don't die,
please don't die, Lord Shogo.

374
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:31,140
Please, please don't leave us.

375
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:35,080
(indistinct conversation)

376
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:39,010
Don't leave us, don't die!

377
00:20:39,010 --> 00:20:40,150
Lord Shogo, Lord Shogo!

378
00:20:40,150 --> 00:20:42,080
You helped us,
how can we help you?

379
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:45,280
Lord Shogo, you've helped us,
protected us for so long.

380
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:48,220
If you leave us, Lord Shogo,
we can't go on without you.

381
00:20:48,220 --> 00:20:50,100
We don't know what to do.

382
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:53,240
No one has ever given so much
to the village of Shimabara.

383
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:57,030
No one has ever cared for us
as much as Lord Shogo has.

384
00:20:57,030 --> 00:21:00,130
Lord Shogo, please
help this old woman.

385
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:02,000
Give me strength.

386
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,120
How can we find a safe
and happy place to live

387
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:07,090
if Lord Shogo's
not around to help?

388
00:21:07,090 --> 00:21:10,050
We need you to live to help us
build our Christian lives.

389
00:21:10,050 --> 00:21:12,170
You must live!

390
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:14,170
Please don't die on us.

391
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:17,170
(indistinct chatter)

392
00:21:17,170 --> 00:21:20,050
♪

393
00:21:20,050 --> 00:21:23,010
(crowd crying)

394
00:21:23,010 --> 00:21:25,030
Lord Shogo, please don't die.

395
00:21:25,030 --> 00:21:28,040
We all need your help and
your guidance in our lives.

396
00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:29,160
We need you.

397
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:34,150
We can't go on
without you, Lord Shogo.

398
00:21:34,150 --> 00:21:39,160
♪

399
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,190
Help us!

400
00:21:40,190 --> 00:21:42,260
Please promise you won't die.

401
00:21:42,260 --> 00:21:45,100
Promise to stay with us.

402
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:49,020
Please, promise you'll live.

403
00:21:49,020 --> 00:21:51,120
I...promise.

404
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,120
(crowd crying)

405
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:55,250
♪

406
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:58,090
Kenshin.

407
00:21:58,090 --> 00:21:59,280
We did it, Kori.

408
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:02,280
(gasping)

409
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:05,180
You can see!

410
00:22:05,180 --> 00:22:07,240
-You can see again!
-It's true.

411
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:11,250
Yes, and you're
a sight for sore eyes.

412
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:13,040
I'm so glad.

413
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,150
♪

414
00:22:15,150 --> 00:22:17,170
I'm so glad!

415
00:22:17,170 --> 00:22:20,280
(crying)

416
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:24,280
Kenshin, I knew that
you could pull it off.

417
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:27,060
Kenshin!

418
00:22:27,060 --> 00:22:29,040
Hey, Kenshin!

419
00:22:29,040 --> 00:22:29,405
What happened?

420
00:22:29,405 --> 00:22:31,200
Did I miss anything, tell me.

421
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:34,170
A miracle happened here,
Misao, a miracle.

422
00:22:34,170 --> 00:22:35,260
And Kenshin did it!

423
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,150
No, the people of
Shimabara did it.

424
00:22:39,150 --> 00:22:41,180
Their love saved
someone who'd forgotten

425
00:22:41,180 --> 00:22:43,270
what it's like to be a man,

426
00:22:43,270 --> 00:22:47,040
but now, Shogo Amakusa
is finally home.

427
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:55,200
♪

428
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:58,060
(singing in foreign language)

429
00:22:58,060 --> 00:25:12,290
♪

